EucaTest version 0.01
=====================

EucaTest is an attempt to leverage existing test code to make test writing faster.

DEPENDENCIES

This module requires these other modules and libraries:

  IO::Pty
  Net:OpenSSH

CREATING YOUR LOCAL TEST CREATION ENVIRONMENT

1) Install Eclipse
2) Install the EPIC Perl Plugin
	- Select Help > Software Updates... in Eclipse, add the update site http://e-p-i-c.sf.net/updates/testing and follow the on-screen instructions.
3) Create test-area
	 mkdir test-area;
	 cd test-area
	 mkdir input; mkdir stage; mkdir share;
	 cd share; mkdir perl_lib; 
	 git clone https://viglesiasce@bitbucket.org/viglesiasce/eucatest.git
	 mv eucatest EucaTest
4) Download the run_instance.pl script from https://bitbucket.org/viglesiasce/eucatest/downloads/run_instance.pl
5) Copy that file to test-area/stage and make it executable
6) Run that file to ensure the environment has been setup properly

